The paper focuses on deep learning and evolutionary algorithms for unsupervised learning, which are commonly studied in the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), and natural language processing (cs.CL). However, since the paper mainly deals with unsupervised deep neural networks for learning meaningful representations, cs.LG and cs.NE are the most likely sub-categories. The use of labeled data for performance improvement also suggests cs.CV and cs.CL as possible sub-categories.
